Saipem Wins Aramco Contract for Wasit Gas Field Works, MEED Says

-- B y   A n t h o n y   D i P a o l a
-- 
2011-02-27T11:49:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-27/saipem-wins-aramco-contract-for-wasit-gas-field-works-meed-says.html
  Saipem SpA  won a contract that may
be valued at $2.1 billion from Saudi Aramco for offshore works
for the Wasit natural-gas plant development in Saudi Arabia,
MEED reported, without saying where it got the information.  Italy’s Saipem beat  South Korea ’s Hyundai Heavy Industries
Co. to win the engineering, procurement and construction
contract and the award will be announced in March, MEED magazine
said. The Wasit project has an overall value of about $4.6
billion, MEED said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anthony Dipaola in Dubai at 
 adipaola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
 sev@bloomberg.net  